<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns5="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="mdaqAIScanSync">
	<refnamediv>
		<refname>mdaqAIScanSync</refname>
		<refpurpose>Synchronizes analg input conversion with digital input</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>
	
	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>
		<synopsis>
			mdaqAIScanSync(channels, dio, edge)
			mdaqAIScanSync(linkID, channels, dio, edge)
		</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection id="Description_mdaqAIScanSync">
		<title>Description</title>
		<para>
		</para>
	</refsection>  
  
	<refsection id="Parameters_mdaqAIScanSync">
		<title>Input arguments</title>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><para><emphasis role="bold">linkID: </emphasis> Valid connection link id (optional)</para></listitem>
			<listitem><para><emphasis role="bold">dio: </emphasis> Digital input pin (1-8) </para></listitem>
            <listitem><para><emphasis role="bold">edge: </emphasis> Type of digital input signal edge which triggers analog input conversion. 1 - falling edge, 2 - rising edge, 3 - falling or rising edge</para></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</refsection>
	
	<refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        
        <para> Perform blocking data acquisition from 8 single-ended analog input channels, one analog input range. Conversion of analog input is performed on DI 1 falling edge. Note that 
        rate parameter in <link linkend="mdaqAIScanInit">mdaqAIScanInit</link> function is a expected value of conversion rate and is required to read data properly.</para>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
            expectedRate = 10000;
			mdaqAIScanInit(1:8, [-10,10], %F, expectedRate, 1)
	        mdaqAIScanSync(1, 1);	
			plot(mdaqAIScan(10000, -1));
			 ]]>
		</programlisting>
		
    </refsection>
	
